Build passes cleanly. Here's a summary of what `SphereManifold.jsx` implements:

**Left Panel (55%) — Wireframe Sphere:**
- 12 longitude + 11 latitude wireframe lines via `generateWireframe` + `parametricSphere`
- Depth-sorted back-to-front with opacity modulated by z-depth
- Faint filled circle behind wireframe (primary at 6% opacity)
- Auto-rotation at 0.3 rad/s via `requestAnimationFrame`, pauses on drag, resumes after 3s
- Drag-to-rotate: pointer delta maps to rotation at 0.005 rad/px
- Click hit-testing: ray-sphere intersection → inverse rotation → `(u, v)` extraction → `onDotPlace`

**Right Panel (45%) — Two Stereographic Disc Charts:**
- **Chart N** (amber): stereographic projection from north pole, equator at 60% disc radius
- **Chart S** (cyan): stereographic projection from south pole
- Each disc has an 8×8 distortion grid (muted at 15% opacity) showing how the map distorts
- Equatorial overlap band (|lat| < 45°) highlighted in light green on both discs
- Click-to-place on either disc via inverse stereographic projection
- Coordinate readout labels on mapped dots

**Teaching Text:** Updates via `onTeachingText` based on dot latitude (north pole / south pole / equator / default).
